Package arcade.agent.cell

Class TissueCell

java.lang.Object
arcade.agent.cell.TissueCell
All Implemented Interfaces:
Cell, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
Direct Known Subclasses:
TissueHCell
public abstract class TissueCell
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cell
Implementation of Cell for generic tissue cell.

TissueCell agents exist in one of seven states: neutral, apoptotic, quiescent, migratory, proliferative, senescent, and necrotic. The neutral state is an transition state for "undecided" cells, and does not have any biological analog.

TissueCell agents have two required Module types: metabolism and signaling. Metabolism controls changes in cell energy and volume. Signaling controls the proliferative vs. migratory decision.

General order of rules for the TissueCell step:

  • update age
  • check lifespan (possible change to apoptotic)
  • step metabolism module
  • check energy status (possible change to quiescent, necrotic)
  • step signaling module
  • check if neutral (change to proliferative, migratory, senescent)

Cell parameters are tracked using a map between the parameter name and a Parameter object. Daughter cell parameter values are drawn from a distribution centered on the parent cell parameter with the specified amount of heterogeneity.

2.2
Version:
2.3.9

  • Constructor Details

    • TissueCell

      public TissueCell​(int pop, Location loc, double vol, int age, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​Parameter> p)
      Creates a TissueCell agent.

      TissueCell agents are by default assigned as type = neutral and code = healthy. Any extending constructors should change type and/or code as needed.

      Cell parameters are drawn from Parameter distributions. A new map of Parameter objects is created using these values as the new means of the distributions. This cell parameter map is used when constructing daughter cell agents, so any daughter cells will draw their parameter values from the parent distribution (rather than the default distribution). Note that META_PREF and MIGRA_THRESHOLD are assigned to the cell parameter map, but are updated separately by the Module constructors.

      Parameters:
      pop - the population index
      loc - the location of the cell
      vol - the initial (and critical) volume of the cell
      age - the initial age of the cell in minutes
      p - the map of parameter name to Parameter objects
